Business Description and Company Update

AUTO1 Group SE (‚ÄúAUTO1‚Äù or ‚Äúthe Group‚Äù) is Europe‚Äôs largest and most integrated digital used-vehicle trading platform, operating at scale through its Merchant (AUTO1.com) and Retail (Autohero) divisions. Headquartered in Berlin, the Group connects consumers, professional dealers, and institutional investors through a unified data-driven ecosystem that combines online sourcing, refurbishment, logistics, and financing.

‚∏ª

üîπ Customer Journey and Operating Model

AUTO1‚Äôs operating model spans the full vehicle lifecycle:
	1.	Sourcing:
	‚Ä¢	Vehicles are acquired directly from consumers via digital purchasing brands such as wirkaufendeinauto.de (‚ÄúWKDA‚Äù) and through trade-ins or lease returns.
	‚Ä¢	Cars are priced algorithmically using the AUTO1 Pricing Engine, which incorporates over 16 million historical transaction datapoints across 40+ markets to determine fair value and margin potential.
	‚Ä¢	After inspection and acceptance, the vehicle is legally transferred to Auto1 European Cars B.V. (CarCo), which holds title and finances the inventory under the Auto1 Inventory ABS facility.
	2.	Reconditioning and Logistics:
	‚Ä¢	Vehicles are refurbished and quality-checked in one of 13 European logistics and reconditioning hubs, managed centrally through AUTO1‚Äôs proprietary autoFlow operating system.
	‚Ä¢	Cars destined for retail are cosmetically prepared to Autohero standards; those routed for B2B resale are listed on the dealer-facing AUTO1.com platform.
	‚Ä¢	Turnaround time from acquisition to resale typically ranges from 30‚Äì60 days depending on channel and vehicle type.
	3.	Sales and Distribution:
	‚Ä¢	AUTO1.com (Merchant segment): a digital wholesale marketplace connecting ~60,000 registered dealers. Dealers bid for inventory through timed auctions and finance purchases using the Merchant Financing Programme (floorplan lines typically 30‚Äì180 days).
	‚Ä¢	Autohero (Retail segment): an e-commerce platform where end-consumers purchase fully reconditioned cars online with optional home delivery. Retail vehicles are financed on balance sheet until sale, then refinanced via Autohero consumer finance partnerships.
	4.	Collections and Cash Cycle:
	‚Ä¢	Upon sale, proceeds are automatically swept into pledged accounts.
	‚Ä¢	Inventory loans are repaid or re-drawn daily according to the Borrowing-Base within the Auto1 Funding B.V. securitisation structure, providing a fully controlled revolving liquidity loop.

This end-to-end digital process allows AUTO1 to price, fund, and recycle inventory faster than traditional dealerships, creating a scalable liquidity engine for the European used-car market.

‚∏ª

üîπ Funding Architecture

AUTO1‚Äôs balance-sheet light strategy relies on three secured funding pillars:
	1.	Inventory ABS Facility (Auto1 Funding B.V.):
	‚Ä¢	Provides working-capital funding for vehicles held by Auto1 European Cars B.V. (CarCo).
	‚Ä¢	Structured as a multi-tranche note programme (Senior / Mezz / Junior), with daily Borrowing-Base reporting and eligibility tests.
	‚Ä¢	Funding is collateralised by title to vehicles, sale proceeds, and bank accounts, monitored by Cr√©dit Agricole CIB as Agent and Security Trustee.
	‚Ä¢	Facility size post-7th Amendment: ‚Ç¨1.4bn with revolving maturity through 2027.
	2.	Merchant Financing ABS:
	‚Ä¢	Provides inventory credit to professional dealers purchasing via AUTO1.com.
	‚Ä¢	Receivables securitised through a separate SPV; risk transferred off balance sheet.
	3.	Corporate Cash and Equity:
	‚Ä¢	‚Ç¨615m unrestricted cash as of June-2025; net cash position ‚Ç¨343m (vs. ‚Ç¨271m YE-2024).
	‚Ä¢	Listed equity on the Frankfurt Stock Exchange; market capitalisation c.‚Ç¨1.8bn (Aug-2025).

Together, these pillars create a stable, scalable funding structure with low dependency on unsecured debt markets.

‚∏ª

